Explanation:
Let us determine the annual coupon rate. The formula is:
{eq}Coupon\:rate = \dfrac{Coupon\:payment}{Face\:value}

{/eq}
Here, the face value is $1,000 and the coupon payment made every year is $60.
{eq}Coupon\:rate = \dfrac{60}{1,000} \\

Coupon\:rate = 0.06 \:or\:6\text{%}

{/eq}
The coupon rate is
C. 6 percent.

The correct answer to the given question is option
C) 6 %
.
The coupon rate is given by:
{eq}\begin{align*}

&= \dfrac{\text{Coupon payment}}{\text{Face value}} \\[0.3 cm]

&= \dfrac{\$120}{\$2,000} \\[0.3 cm]

&= 6\%

\end{align*}

{/eq}
